			 <NOTE TYPE="summary">This document is a letter written by Governor
				John Sevier (1796-1801, 1803-1809) to Colonel Hugh Montgomery on April 4, 1804.
				The letter states that people have illegally settled on Indian lands and that
				troops are going to be employed to remove them. Sevier instructs Montgomery to
				warn these settlers of the dangers to which they will be exposed if they
				trespass on Indian lands.</NOTE> 
