  <TEXT> 
	 <BODY> 
		<DIV1 TYPE="letter"><PB N="[1]"> 
		  <OPENER> 
			 <ADDRESS> 
				<ADDRLINE> 
				  <NAME TYPE="place">Knoxville</NAME> 
				  <DATE VALUE="1804-04-04">4 April 1804</DATE></ADDRLINE> 
			 </ADDRESS> 
			 <SALUTE>Sir</SALUTE></OPENER> 
		  <P>Permit me to trouble you with An address <ADD
			 PLACE="supralinear">which</ADD> I beg you to forward <ADD
			 PLACE="supralinear">directed</ADD> to the <DEL TYPE="overstrike">inhabit</DEL>
		  people said to be <ADD PLACE="supralinear">settled and</ADD> intruding upon the
		  Indian lands. I am officially informed by the Agent of the War department that
		  there is a considerable number of <DEL TYPE="overstrike">those</DEL> persons
		  settled on those lands, and I also understand that the regular troops
		  <ADD PLACE="supralinear">are shortly</ADD> <DEL TYPE="overstrike">is
		  about</DEL> to be employed for their removal I <ADD
		  PLACE="supralinear">therefore</ADD> deem it expedient to <DEL
		  TYPE="overstrike"><ORIG REG="forewarn">fore warn</ORIG> them</DEL> give them
		  information of the dangers they may <DEL TYPE="overstrike">be</DEL> expose<DEL
		  TYPE="overstrike">d</DEL> themselves to, should they be found trespassing as
		  has been to me represented</P> 
		  <CLOSER> 
			 <SALUTE>I have the honor &amp; 
				<ABBR EXPAN="et cetera">C</ABBR></SALUTE> 
			 <SIGNED> 
				<NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="John">J.</ABBR> Sevier</NAME> 
				<ADDRESS> 
				  <ADDRLINE> 
					 <NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="Colonel">Colo.</ABBR> Hugh
						Montgomery</NAME></ADDRLINE> 
				  <ADDRLINE> 
					 <NAME TYPE="place">Anderson County</NAME>&mdash;
					 &rcub;</ADDRLINE> 
				</ADDRESS> </SIGNED></CLOSER> 
		</DIV1> 
	 </BODY> 
